22 October 2020 In our post Cabinet media briefing earlier today, we announced that Cabinet had appointed Ms Jennifer Schreiner as a Non-executive member to the Board of Control of the Passenger Rail Agency of South Africa (PRASA). In making this assertion, we relied on an outdated Cabinet Memo which has since been updated. The updated Memo lists Ms Nosizwe Nokwe-Macamo as part of the collective appointed to the Board. The updated list of Non-executive members appointed to the Board of Control of PRASA is as follows: a. Mr Leonard Ramatlakane (Chairperson)b. Adv Smanga Sethenec. Mr Matodzi Mukhuba d. Ms Boitumelo Mokgokoe. Mr Dinkwanyane K Mohubaf. Dr Alison E Lewisg. Ms Nosizwe Nokwe-Macamoh. Ms Thinavhuyo N Mpyei. Representative from the Department of Transportj. Representative from the Department of Financek. Representative from the South African Local Government Association We profusely apologise for any confusion and inconvenience caused. Enquiries:Phumla WilliamsCell: 083 501 0139